   <caption>Binomial Identities of the Dot Product Operation</caption>
   <statement.theorem>
      <para>
         <para.body>For vectors <math>
               <latex>\Vect{x}</latex>
            </math> and <math>
               <latex>\Vect{y}</latex>
            </math> in <math>
               <latex>\RNr[n]</latex>
            </math> the following binomial identities hold:</para.body>
         <index.glossary>
            <term>dot product</term>
            <term>binomial identities</term>
            <info>
               <para>
                  <para.body>Click for the proposition formulating basic properties of the dot product operation</para.body>
               </para>
            </info>
         </index.glossary>
      </para>
      <part.theorem partid="Prop_DotProductSumSquared">
         <part.body>
            <math.display>
               <latex>
					
					\aligned
					\DotPr{ (\Vect{x} + \Vect{y}) }{ (\Vect{x} + \Vect{y}) } &amp;= \DotPr{ \Vect{x} }{ \Vect{x} } + 2(\DotPr{ \Vect{x} }{ \Vect{y} }) + \DotPr{ \Vect{y} }{ \Vect{y} } \\
					\DotPr{ (\Vect{x} - \Vect{y}) }{ (\Vect{x} - \Vect{y}) } &amp;= \DotPr{ \Vect{x} }{ \Vect{x} } - 2(\DotPr{ \Vect{x} }{ \Vect{y} }) + \DotPr{ \Vect{y} }{ \Vect{y} }
					\endaligned

				</latex>
            </math.display>
         </part.body>
      </part.theorem>
      <part.theorem partid="Prop_DotProductSumTimesDifference">
         <part.body>
            <math.display>
               <latex>\DotPr{ (\Vect{x} + \Vect{y}) }{ (\Vect{x} - \Vect{y}) } = \DotPr{ \Vect{x} }{ \Vect{x} } - \DotPr{ \Vect{y} }{ \Vect{y} }</latex>
            </math.display>
         </part.body>
      </part.theorem>
   </statement.theorem>
   <proof type="Proof">
      <proof.block>
         <para>
            <para.body>Each of these identities follows by computing both sides of the given equation, and checking that the results are equal. Here we rely on the basic algebraic properties of the dot product.</para.body>
         </para>
         <logic>
            <part.ref>Prop_DotProductSumSquared</part.ref>
         </logic>
         <caption>
			This binomial identity holds because
		</caption>
